parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, and can also result in uneven tire wear, reduced vehicle stability, and difficulty steering.
symptoms: The steering wheel becomes difficult to maneuver
there is an abnormal clicking sound heard from the steering wheel
the vehicle shakes or vibrates
the tire blows out
the steering wheel jerks
and the vehicle stalls without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, and can also result in uneven tire wear, reduced vehicle stability, and difficulty steering.
symptoms: The rear suspension bottoms out
there is a loud grinding noise
the vehicle flips over
the rear suspension bangs
and the vehicle feels like it's driving on wooden wheels.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Cruise Control and Brake Pedal Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The issues with the cruise control and brake pedal can cause accidents, as the driver may not be able to properly control the vehicle.
symptoms: The cruise control is difficult to release
the brake pedal has to be pressed excessively to disengage cruise control
and the vehicle stalls without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Lower Radiator Support and Front Cross Frame Tie Bar
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the lower radiator support and front cross frame tie bar can lead to a loss of structural integrity, potentially causing the engine to fall out of place, the hood to pop open while driving, and unstable front-end control, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Rusting or corrosion of the lower radiator support and front cross frame tie bar
excessive rusting on the frame below the radiator
rusting through of the structural member
hole development at the mounting area
excessive up/down movement of the engine compartment's hood
and vibration of the hood at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly without pressing the accelerator pedal
the accelerator pedal becomes stuck
the vehicle surges forward
the engine RPM increases rapidly
the vehicle speed increases uncontrollably
the brake pedal is ineffective
and the cruise control system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Idle speed control defects can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to loss of power steering and braking ability, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls randomly
especially when stopping at stoplights or backing out of parking lots
the idle speed control valve is defective
and the electronic control module may be defective.
